main event: A civilian observed a round object that changed to a cigar-shape, yellow in color, that occasionally changed shape and brightness, moving from the north-northeast to the east at an estimated 25,000 feet with no reported sound.
interesting points: The object was initially round, then changed to a cigar-shape.
The object changed shape and brightness occasionally.
The object was estimated to be at 25,000 feet altitude.
No speed was reported for the object.
The winds were described as relatively light.
